HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 120
BY REPRESENTATIVE LYONS
INSURANCE: Creates the PACE Task Force to prioritize access, care, and education on
GLP-1 medications
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To create and establish the PACE Task Force to prioritize access, care, and education on
3 GLP-1 medications by studying their clinical history, accessibility, and effect on
4 insurance costs for insureds and insurers in this state and to report their written
5 findings to the legislature.
6 WHEREAS, Glucagon-like peptide or GLP-1 receptor agonist medications
7 introduced in 2005 for Type 2 diabetes, have rapidly evolved into revolutionary treatments
8 for chronic weight management following a series of landmark United States Food and Drug
9 Administration approvals; and
10 WHEREAS, this state played a pivotal role in the scientific foundation of these
11 drugs, heavily contributing to the research and development of GLP-1s as groundbreaking
12 obesity treatments; and
13 WHEREAS, following these advancements, this state experienced an explosion in
14 demand, highlighted by a roughly eight thousand eight hundred percent increase in
15 prescription requests within the state's Medicaid plans between July 2022 and January 2023;
16 and
17 WHEREAS, GLP-1 drugs have largely replaced traditional diabetes medications,
18 causing a massive price jump from roughly twenty dollars per month to over one thousand
19 two hundred dollars per month, straining state-sponsored insurance plans and driving
20 millions of dollars in unexpected costs; and
