1 WHEREAS, despite explicitly prohibiting coverage for GLP-1s strictly indicated for
2 obesity treatment, Louisiana still expends two hundred million dollars annually on these
3 medications for diabetic members, while access for primary weight management remains
4 heavily restricted due to a sixteen thousand dollar annual cost per patient; and
5 WHEREAS, currently, Louisiana Medicaid covers GLP-1 medications only if the
6 patient has a qualifying body mass index and co-occurring conditions like type 2 diabetes
7 exist; and
8 WHEREAS, newer oral (pill) forms of GLP-1 receptor agonist drugs are available
9 for weight loss and type 2 diabetes management, eliminating the need for weekly injections;
10 and
11 WHEREAS, oral (pill) forms of GLP-1 medications approved through 2025 offer a
12 non-injectable alternative, yet they fail to offer cost savings as they are priced on par with
13 injectables, continuing to drive up commercial health insurance premiums; and
14 WHEREAS, to manage these extreme pharmacy benefit expenditures, public and
15 private insurers in 2026 are scaling back benefits, implementing strict utilization
16 management, such as prior authorizations and step-therapy rules, or terminating weight-loss
17 coverage entirely, leaving millions without access; and
18 WHEREAS, while the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS) has
19 introduced temporary bridge demonstrations offering select products at a fifty-dollar
20 monthly copay for eligible beneficiaries, broader structural coverage solutions are urgently
21 needed; and
22 WHEREAS, Louisiana must conduct a comprehensive evaluation of GLP-1
23 utilization and actuarial dynamics to develop sustainable solutions that expand necessary
24 healthcare access while protecting the fiscal health of the state and its citizens.
25 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
26 create and establish the PACE Task Force to study the history, accessibility, and insurance
27 costs of GLP-1 medications and to propose specific recommendations for legislation.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the legislature recommends that the PACE Task
29 Force, in its consideration, include but not be limited to the following topics:
