1 (1) Whether GLP-1 medication pricing should differ for diabetes versus weight loss
2 indications.
3 (2) Whether plans covering GLP-1 medications attract higher-risk enrollees.
4 (3) Whether strict approval policies reduce insurer spending or shift costs elsewhere.
5 (4) Whether, and to what extent, employers restrict GLP-1 coverage to control
6 premium growth.
7 (5) Whether lower-income or uninsured populations disproportionately are excluded
8 due to costs.
9 (6) Causes why an insured or enrollee may discontinue GLP-1 medications after
10 only months of treatment.
11 (7) Actuarial projection models showing long-term net savings of GLP-1 coverage
12 over two, five, and ten years.
13 (8) Which form of GLP-1 medication is more cost-effective?
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
15 members:
16 (1) The commissioner of insurance or his designee.
17 (2) The chief executive officer of the Louisiana Association of Health Plans or his
18 designee.
19 (3) The secretary of the Louisiana Department of Health or his designee.
20 (4) The chair of the Louisiana Board of Pharmacy or his designee.
21 (5) One representative that is a licensed healthcare provider who specializes in
22 endocrinology and obesity from a list of nominees submitted by Our Lady of the Lake,
23 Baton Rouge Clinic, or Woman's Metabolic Center appointed by the speaker of the House
24 of Representatives.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall be staffed by the Louisiana
26 Department of Insurance.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that each designating authority shall submit the
28 names of designees to the task force to the Louisiana Department of Insurance no later than
29 August 1, 2026.
